INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (905, 2, '2010-03-24 08:00:09', '2010-03-24 07:00:09', 'Batman and Chatroulette, a winning combination. And before you aks, yes I bought the domain name. That’s how funny I think this really is. I know it\'s just the new hype, but Chatroulette really lends itself superbly for making comics.\r\n\r\nIf the last comic doesn’t really make sense to you, it’s tied to <a target="_blank" href="http://batman.wikia.com/wiki/Thomas_Wayne">the death of Bruce Wayne’s (Batman’s) parents</a>. In most versions, they were shot after taking young Bruce out to see The Mark of Zorro at the cinema. \r\n\r\nThat’s it for this week. Check back next Wednesday for some more Batroulette!', '091 - Batroulette', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '091-batroulette', '', '', '2010-03-24 20:16:04', '2010-03-24 19:16:04', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=905', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (910, 2, '2010-03-31 08:00:10', '2010-03-31 06:00:10', 'Back with some Batman vs. Chatroulette. These are so much fun to make!\r\nIf you missed it, be sure to check out <a href="http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/news/091-batroulette">last week’s installment</a>.', '092 - Batroulette part 2', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '092-batroulette-part-2', '', '', '2010-03-31 08:49:52', '2010-03-31 06:49:52', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=910', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (929, 2, '2010-04-07 07:00:50', '2010-04-07 05:00:50', 'You’re in for a treat (almost wrote ‘threat’ there, hehe). April is guest month here at Beardfluff headquarters and we’re starting with Lucas Dewilde.\r\n\r\nLucas is a man of many talents: a <a target="_blank" href="http://wildt.be/">grahic designer</a>, <a href="http://wildt.be/verwilderd/art.html" target="_blank">graphic artist</a>, all-round twisted individual with a near encyclopedic knowledge of music (and a huge record collection) and a poet. Reasons enough to want to share his work here.\r\n\r\nOh, and if you haven’t already, be sure to join the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Beardfluff/102819556426508">new Facebook Fan Page</a> for a chance to win beardy prizes!\r\n ', 'Guest month - mr. Migraine', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guestmonth-mrmigraine', '', '', '2010-11-25 22:36:38', '2010-11-25 21:36:38', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=929', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (948, 2, '2010-04-14 07:00:01', '2010-04-14 05:00:01', 'This week’s guestcomic offers a look into the everyday life of The Greatest Beard. It comes from Philippa Rice of <a href="http://mycardboardlife.com/" target="_blank">My Cardboard Life</a> fame. As you can see, her comics are quite different from most. No pencils or inks here. Instead each comic is carefully handcrafted out of paper, cardboard and wittiness.\r\n\r\nBy the way, the Beardfluff Facebook Page <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Beardfluff/102819556426508" target="_blank">mini-contest</a> is closed. Winners will be picked later today.\r\n', 'Guest month - Stressed out', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guest-month-stressed-out', '', '', '2010-11-25 22:35:35', '2010-11-25 21:35:35', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=948', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (955, 2, '2010-04-21 07:30:51', '2010-04-21 05:30:51', 'Hello and welcome to the folks coming in via Eardrums! Hope you enjoy the show.\r\nIf you don\'t know what I\'m talking about, I recently made a comic for the booklet of a music compilation called ‘Between the Waves’. It’s a free release from <a href="http://www.eardrumspop.com/releases-2/" target="_blank">Eardrums Pop</a> that you can download <a href="http://www.eardrumspop.com/2010/04/19/b2wvola/" target="_blank">right here</a>. There\'s 3 parts to the compilation, but the booklet is included in this part A. The comic provides some backstory to ‘The Greatest Beard’ and talks about the spirit of coöperation (sort of :).\r\n\r\nThere\'s been a little hickup in the Guest Month so I\'ll have to leave you with a filler and the news above. Hope to get things sorted by next Wednesday though. These are some beards I drew for the winners of the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Beardfluff/102819556426508">Facebook Fanpage</a> competion last week. ', 'Filler - Custom beards', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'filler-custom-beards', '', '', '2010-07-20 17:00:07', '2010-07-20 15:00:07', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=955', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (976, 2, '2010-04-28 07:50:42', '2010-04-28 05:50:42', 'This piece of art comes from the talented <a target="_blank" href="http://twitter.com/joe_hunter">Joe Hunter</a>, who\'s comics you can admire over at <a target="_blank" href="http://journalincomix.wordpress.com/">Journalin Comix</a>. His style is perhaps best described as ‘Insane hobo rambling’, so it won\'t surprise anyone that I was immediately hooked and commissioned a piece when I had the chance.', 'Guest month - Bearded Batman', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guest-month-bearded-batman', '', '', '2010-07-20 17:21:11', '2010-07-20 15:21:11', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=976', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 1); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (989, 2, '2010-05-05 08:00:03', '2010-05-05 06:00:03', '<p>Guest month has come and gone, so here I am, back with new comics! This month is also <a href="http://moustachemay.com/" target="_blank">Moustache May</a>. A fine reason to wear my favorite shirt: Captain Teacup.</p>\r\n<p>The moustached cup is one of mr. John Allison’s shirt designs (of <a href="http://www.scarygoround.com/" target="_blank">Scary-go-Round</a> and <a href="http://badmachinery.com/" target="_blank">Bad Machinery</a> fame of course). Unfortunately, it seems to be out of stock permanently so you can\'t have it. I urge you all to protest the loss of such a fine piece of decorative clothing and mail the master to plead for it’s return. I kinda need a back up in case I wear it out.</p>\r\n<p>In other news, I now have mini comics for sale <a href="http://beardfluff.bigcartel.com" target="_blank">in the shop</a>. Be sure to check that out.</p>\r\n', '093 - Desorientation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '093-desorientation', '', '', '2010-07-21 23:51:41', '2010-07-21 21:51:41', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=989', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1007, 2, '2010-05-12 07:30:28', '2010-05-12 05:30:28', 'My greatest enemy is probably indecision. The struggle to figure out what I should do first with my time has cost me many hours, either sitting around paralyzed or walking back and forth in frustration. One of my many artistic (autistic, really) traits.\r\n\r\nI thought I\'d go for some dramatic lighting and coloring here, it seemed fitting and I had some time for experimenting. I like the use of textures, gradients & highlights that I\'ve been seeing in a lot of comics lately (like ‘Wormwood: Gentleman corpse’ or ‘The Surrogates’) but that may be a bit too dirty for me. We\'ll see, I need to play more with coloring anyway.\r\n\r\nAlso, you\'ll notice a change in page orientation. After the cost and problems with printing up some square comics (<a href="http://beardfluff.bigcartel.com" target="_blank">available right here by the way</a>) I thought I\'d make some comics in a more standard size. It’ll force me to change my writing a bit as well, which is never a bad idea. Getting a bit tired of the horizontal strip.', '094 - Indecision', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '094-indecision', '', '', '2010-05-12 07:51:42', '2010-05-12 05:51:42', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=1007', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 8); 
INSERT INTO `wp090901_posts` VALUES (1031, 2, '2010-05-19 07:30:01', '2010-05-19 05:30:01', 'Twice I’ve been attacked by a pigeon by now. Sure, people will tell you it’s because of the reflection in the window and birds think it\'s just open space but I imagine those pigeons are after my life. And really, wouldn’t you if you were in their stead? No one in a city seems to like them. Sure, they’re disease-ridden vermin, but they don’t like that any more than we do. So next time you see a pigeon feeding, don’t try to kick it, alright?\r\n\r\nBy the way, the <a href="http://paperblackninja.com/downloads/beards/" target="_blank">free beards</a> are still up for download (until Sunday) and <a href="http://beardfluff.bigcartel.com" target="_blank">Beardfluff comics</a> are still available in the store.', '095 - Dive bomb', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '095-dive-bomb', '', '', '2010-07-21 23:51:20', '2010-07-21 21:51:20', '', 0, 'http://paperblackninja.com/beardfluff/?p=1031', 0, 'webcomic_post', '', 0); 
